  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_321047423" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/321047423" />
    <a title="Kylie Luebbering" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6492693-kylie-luebbering"><img alt="Kylie Luebbering" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/321047423?book_show_action=true">Apr 29, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kylie Luebbering" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kylie Luebbering" href="/user/show/6492693-kylie-luebbering">Kylie Luebbering</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer321047423" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12740997511893843891">I adored reading this incredible novel, it is a fantastic book with a fascinating tale of highschool romance. It&apos;s about a young man who falls head over heels for the &quot;perfect&quot; girl. Sage seems to be just that, and appears to have it all, but there is something she&apos;d like to change, her true gender. Sage is a male-born transgender, who keeps her secret in fear of people&apos;s reactions. <br/>Author Brian Katcher had never been known to be involved with LGBT novels. He is recorded in an interview as being</span>
  <span id="freeText12740997511893843891" style="display:none">I adored reading this incredible novel, it is a fantastic book with a fascinating tale of highschool romance. It's about a young man who falls head over heels for the "perfect" girl. Sage seems to be just that, and appears to have it all, but there is something she'd like to change, her true gender. Sage is a male-born transgender, who keeps her secret in fear of people's reactions. <br />Author Brian Katcher had never been known to be involved with LGBT novels. He is recorded in an interview as being tired of traditional romance stories with everything going perfectly. He is thrilled by the reactions, especially the LGBT community. Katcher has received the ALA award, the Stonewall Award for Children's and YA Book. Writing this novel has inspired Katcher to begin writing more of this genre. <br />While reading this story, I kept thinking back to the episode of MTV's Truelife: I'm a Transgender. In that episode, a male- born transgender is terrified of how people would react of they found out her secret. It's so similar to Sage's fears and rationales in Almost Perfect. <br />I would recommend this novel to any of my peers who enjoy reading teen novels, because this one stands out. It's a traditional highschool love story with a huge twist. It's so relatable to the world today, with people being so much more excepting of the LGBT community. I loved this book, I could not put it down. Katcher is definately one of my favorite authors now. :) </span>
  <a data-text-id="12740997511893843891" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

