      <div class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/work/quotes/6155884-almost-perfect">Quotes from Almost Perfect</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Everyone has that one line they swear they'll never cross, the one thing they say they'll never do. Not something serious like <i>I'll never kill anyone</i> or <i>I'll never invade Russia in the winter</i>. Usually, it's something less earth-shattering.<br /><i>I'll never cheat on her.</i><br /><i>I'll never work at a job I hate.</i><br /><i>I'll never give up on my dreams.</i><br />We draw the line. Maybe we even believe it. That's why it's so hard when we break that promise we make to ourselves.<br />Sage Hendricks was my line.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/502966-everyone-has-that-one-line-they-swear-they-ll-never-cross">19 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Sage would survive. I'd survive. We were better off apart. Painful and quick, just like ripping off a Band-Aid. Well, more like gouging a piece of shrapnel out of my stomach, pouring a bottle of gin into the wound, lighting it on fire, and sewing my guts up with a dirty bootlace. But the concept was the same.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
